261
00:24:19.547 --> 00:24:22.507
Maybe I could loosen them up a bit.

262
00:24:37.732 --> 00:24:41.818
You got a great lawyer there.
Top of the line. Here you go.

263
00:25:00.421 --> 00:25:02.589
He's in here!

264
00:25:05.426 --> 00:25:07.403
Jesus!

265
00:25:07.428 --> 00:25:09.071
How y'all doing?

266
00:25:09.096 --> 00:25:10.823
Not again. Carlson!

267
00:25:10.848 --> 00:25:12.742
The guy body-slammed me. sir.

268
00:25:12.767 --> 00:25:13.993
Maybe he likes you.

269
00:25:14.018 --> 00:25:15.411
He did what to you?

270
00:25:15.436 --> 00:25:19.499
Get him out of here! What were
you thinking? Man. that's not smart!

271
00:25:19.524 --> 00:25:21.858
Get him out of here.

272
00:25:23.569 --> 00:25:26.196
What the hell happened up there?

273
00:25:26.197 --> 00:25:28.365
Up here?

274
00:25:28.658 --> 00:25:31.844
I caught him trying to escape.

275
00:25:31.869 --> 00:25:34.329
Who the hell are you?

276
00:25:34.831 --> 00:25:37.225
Malone. Just transferred.
Right there.

277
00:25:37.250 --> 00:25:39.393
Yeah. check that out. Bam!

278
00:25:39.418 --> 00:25:40.812
You know Malone?
- No.

279
00:25:40.837 --> 00:25:43.338
Nobody told me about it.

280
00:25:43.714 --> 00:25:45.924
Guys...

281
00:25:46.717 --> 00:25:47.860
Sorry. ma'am.

282
00:25:47.885 --> 00:25:50.595
Excuse me.

283
00:25:51.305 --> 00:25:54.224
Let me flush. please.

284
00:25:56.686 --> 00:26:01.231
I didn't know.
You might not wanna go in there.

285
00:26:02.525 --> 00:26:06.027
You got some paperwork for me. Malone?

286
00:26:06.153 --> 00:26:09.340
We've been requesting
a new detective for 8 months.

287
00:26:09.365 --> 00:26:14.452
Suddenly. you just turn up.
I'll never understand the system.

288
00:26:14.495 --> 00:26:18.599
Burglary? 16 citations.
mayor's commendation.

289
00:26:18.624 --> 00:26:21.227
You worked out of West Covina?

290
00:26:21.252 --> 00:26:23.938
Well. that's what it says right there.

291
00:26:23.963 --> 00:26:27.632
You look familiar. Malone.
Have we met before?

292
00:26:30.094 --> 00:26:33.972
You wouldn't happen to be
in a bowling league. would you?

293
00:26:35.141 --> 00:26:37.910
That's it. You're a bowler.

294
00:26:37.935 --> 00:26:38.953
I try.

295
00:26:38.978 --> 00:26:41.730
We could use a guy in Burglary.

296
00:26:42.732 --> 00:26:44.292
Right here.

297
00:26:44.317 --> 00:26:49.005
I thought I was gonna be assigned
to a desk. Right up in here!

298
00:26:49.030 --> 00:26:50.339
Are you kidding me?

299
00:26:50.364 --> 00:26:54.010
A guy like you?
No. you belong on the street.

300
00:26:54.035 --> 00:26:55.219
And also. listen.

301
00:26:55.244 --> 00:26:59.557
Carlson needs a partner with some
experience. He just got promoted.

302
00:26:59.582 --> 00:27:01.267
Chief. I just got a call.

303
00:27:01.292 --> 00:27:04.920
Malone's gonna join us.
Show him around.

304
00:27:05.713 --> 00:27:09.257
And let Malone do
all the handcuffing. okay?

305
00:27:09.842 --> 00:27:11.819
I appreciate that. yeah.

306
00:27:11.844 --> 00:27:13.720
I'll review these.

307
00:27:15.723 --> 00:27:18.451
This is the bullpen here.
That's Booking up there.

308
00:27:18.476 --> 00:27:21.829
The holding cells are down that way.
You wanna see them?

309
00:27:21.854 --> 00:27:24.373
Seen one. seen them all.

310
00:27:24.398 --> 00:27:26.000
This is my desk here. sir.

311
00:27:26.025 --> 00:27:27.585
Nice desk.

312
00:27:27.610 --> 00:27:30.338
Thanks. Let's see...

313
00:27:30.363 --> 00:27:31.672
Brass is on 5.

314
00:27:31.697 --> 00:27:33.216
Robbery-Homicide on 3.

315
00:27:33.241 --> 00:27:36.284
Over there. that's the tag and bag.

316
00:27:36.619 --> 00:27:40.288
Through those doors. that's 10-17.
- Roger.

317
00:27:40.665 --> 00:27:42.183
Show him the rest later.

318
00:27:42.208 --> 00:27:44.018
Come on.
- Where?

319
00:27:44.043 --> 00:27:46.979
We got a call. Burglary.
It's ours. I'll take this.

320
00:27:47.004 --> 00:27:48.022
Outside?

321
00:27:48.047 --> 00:27:49.899
That's where all the crime is.

322
00:27:49.924 --> 00:27:52.318
I just got here.
and that's not a good thing.

323
00:27:52.343 --> 00:27:55.988
I gotta do work in here so that
I know what's going on out there.

324
00:27:56.013 --> 00:27:58.640
I might need backup. right?

325
00:28:00.226 --> 00:28:02.161
How long you been in Burglary?

326
00:28:02.186 --> 00:28:04.997
Me? All my life. man. all my life.

327
00:28:05.022 --> 00:28:10.419
I heard the chief say that you got 16
citations. That's incredible! 16!

328
00:28:10.444 --> 00:28:14.698
That's what happens when
your Uncle Lou writes your file.

329
00:28:16.868 --> 00:28:20.328
You can ride up front if you want.

330
00:28:21.038 --> 00:28:22.682
I knew that.

331
00:28:22.707 --> 00:28:26.477
You just gotta be real careful
for the pedestrians coming out here.

332
00:28:26.502 --> 00:28:28.980
Walking around out here.

333
00:28:29.005 --> 00:28:33.466
Am I clear to the right?
Am I clear? Have I got it?

334
00:28:35.469 --> 00:28:36.946
I just made detective.

335
00:28:36.971 --> 00:28:39.097
No kidding.

336
00:28:39.432 --> 00:28:43.977
I worked Traffic for 3 years.
I got pretty good at it.

337
00:28:45.813 --> 00:28:50.668
You don't have to stop for the yellow.
You could just drive right through.

338
00:28:50.693 --> 00:28:56.424
Sir. not if you'd seen some
of the accidents I've seen. No thanks.

339
00:28:56.449 --> 00:28:59.743
Well. there's your green right there.

340
00:29:02.663 --> 00:29:04.474
Can I ask you a personal question?

341
00:29:04.499 --> 00:29:06.851
Yeah. sure.

342
00:29:06.876 --> 00:29:09.794
How many times did you take the test?

343
00:29:10.087 --> 00:29:11.189
What test?

344
00:29:11.214 --> 00:29:14.484
You know. the test for detective.

345
00:29:14.509 --> 00:29:15.902
That one!

346
00:29:15.927 --> 00:29:17.737
One time.
- Really?

347
00:29:17.762 --> 00:29:20.031
Aced it.

348
00:29:20.056 --> 00:29:21.699
Took it out.

349
00:29:21.724 --> 00:29:24.452
Took me 5 tries.

350
00:29:24.477 --> 00:29:28.664
I did well on the written part. but
my performance reviews weren't so hot.

351
00:29:28.689 --> 00:29:32.543
How many times did it take you
to get your driver's license. man?

352
00:29:32.568 --> 00:29:35.505
Please! Wake me up when we get there.

353
00:29:35.530 --> 00:29:37.465
Yes. sir. I'm sorry.

354
00:29:37.490 --> 00:29:40.408
Goodness. man!

355
00:29:40.493 --> 00:29:43.012
It's a nice suit. sir.
It's really cool.

356
00:29:43.037 --> 00:29:44.889
Well. I appreciate it.

357
00:29:44.914 --> 00:29:47.141
Yeah. you know? Appreciate it.

358
00:29:47.166 --> 00:29:48.184
Got any music?

359
00:29:48.209 --> 00:29:50.728
Oh. yeah. Sure.

360
00:29:50.753 --> 00:29:52.271
I like to jam.

361
00:29:52.296 --> 00:29:56.007
Just so long as
we can hear the dispatcher.

362
00:29:56.425 --> 00:29:58.569
That's good.

363
00:29:58.594 --> 00:30:03.557
I never heard this station before.
- Kind of funky. You like that?

364
00:30:14.235 --> 00:30:18.047
Last night these shelves were loaded
with Elites. Now they're gone.

365
00:30:18.072 --> 00:30:19.799
3 dozen gorgeous rims.

366
00:30:19.824 --> 00:30:21.551
They didn't take anything else?

367
00:30:21.576 --> 00:30:26.705
They went for my good stuff. Chrome
with gold trim. 5 grand worth.

368
00:30:26.706 --> 00:30:28.015
What about the alarm?

369
00:30:28.040 --> 00:30:30.101
What about it? It went off.

370
00:30:30.126 --> 00:30:32.436
But it took you guys 2 hours to get here.

371
00:30:32.461 --> 00:30:34.856
My wheels are probably in Tijuana by now.

372
00:30:34.881 --> 00:30:37.424
Here's where they came in.

373
00:30:37.758 --> 00:30:42.488
Looks like they broke the glass. opened
the handle. crawled in the window.

374
00:30:42.513 --> 00:30:43.739
Exactly.

375
00:30:43.764 --> 00:30:45.867
Shimmied down the shelf or something.

376
00:30:45.892 --> 00:30:47.285
This is a waste of time.

377
00:30:47.310 --> 00:30:49.453
That's not how they got in.

378
00:30:49.478 --> 00:30:51.038
Of course it is.

379
00:30:51.063 --> 00:30:53.291
Cut it out.
That's not how they got in.

380
00:30:53.316 --> 00:30:54.625
This is the spot here.

381
00:30:54.650 --> 00:30:57.128
That's how I would've came in.

382
00:30:57.153 --> 00:30:59.172
If I was a thief.

383
00:30:59.197 --> 00:31:01.132
If I was a thief!

384
00:31:01.157 --> 00:31:04.302
Skylight. Just cut the alarm
from the inside.

385
00:31:04.327 --> 00:31:06.304
I could take my time.

386
00:31:06.329 --> 00:31:07.847
Why take your time?

387
00:31:07.872 --> 00:31:10.415
Why would I take my time?

388
00:31:14.212 --> 00:31:16.439
It's heavy.

389
00:31:16.464 --> 00:31:18.149
Now. you tell me.

390
00:31:18.174 --> 00:31:23.112
How long would it take to carry 3 dozen
of those out and load them in a truck?

391
00:31:23.137 --> 00:31:26.115
Long time.
- It would take a very long time.

392
00:31:26.140 --> 00:31:29.785
But they probably had 3
or 4 guys working the damn thing...

393
00:31:29.810 --> 00:31:32.455
Zip! Zip the shit up! Frank. hush.

394
00:31:32.480 --> 00:31:34.874
Because you know better. Come on.

395
00:31:34.899 --> 00:31:39.003
Don't lie to me. I'm the man.
I'm the man. Frank.

396
00:31:39.028 --> 00:31:40.963
You're the man.

397
00:31:40.988 --> 00:31:45.718
Your 5.000. sorry to tell you.
is worth less than 2 on the street.

398
00:31:45.743 --> 00:31:49.680
Which don't go 4 ways
with much juice once you rent a truck.

399
00:31:49.705 --> 00:31:54.185
And to rent a truck. that requires what?

400
00:31:54.210 --> 00:31:56.354
Credit card...

401
00:31:56.379 --> 00:31:59.398
...driver's license.

402
00:31:59.423 --> 00:32:01.984
Unless. of course...

403
00:32:02.009 --> 00:32:04.553
...you got your own truck.

404
00:32:05.596 --> 00:32:07.824
He's not gonna let us search his truck.

405
00:32:07.849 --> 00:32:10.868
What you mean. "let us"? We the police.

406
00:32:10.893 --> 00:32:12.912
We need a warrant to do that.

407
00:32:12.937 --> 00:32:15.981
We don't even need a key.

408
00:32:16.941 --> 00:32:20.419
Detective. you can't do that.
It's unconstitutional.

409
00:32:20.444 --> 00:32:24.614
Look at that. Look at this.

410
00:32:27.326 --> 00:32:28.344
Look.

411
00:32:28.369 --> 00:32:31.472
Solved the crime
my first day on the job!

412
00:32:31.497 --> 00:32:33.015
We bad detectives.

413
00:32:33.040 --> 00:32:34.142
There they are!

414
00:32:34.167 --> 00:32:39.045
Filing a false report
is a very serious crime.

415
00:32:41.257 --> 00:32:45.802
I'll handle this.
Bring your weeble-wobble ass over here.

416
00:32:47.054 --> 00:32:49.991
You like snacks?
- Nothing makes me happier.

417
00:32:50.016 --> 00:32:53.828
You'll be snacking on the bottom
of this shoe if this happens again.

418
00:32:53.853 --> 00:32:55.580
Now. you see them ridges?

419
00:32:55.605 --> 00:32:58.833
These ridges will be imprinted
on the back of your ass...

420
00:32:58.858 --> 00:33:01.502
...permanently if this happens again.

421
00:33:01.527 --> 00:33:02.753
You understand?

422
00:33:02.778 --> 00:33:04.130
Thoroughly understand you.

423
00:33:04.155 --> 00:33:08.176
Every time you look at your ass
there's gonna be a print there.

424
00:33:08.201 --> 00:33:10.678
It's gonna remind you of us.

425
00:33:10.703 --> 00:33:12.805
And of you lying.
- Right.

426
00:33:12.830 --> 00:33:14.515
Don't wanna see those ridges.

427
00:33:14.540 --> 00:33:19.145
Stop eating cold cuts because
it's seeping through your pores.

428
00:33:19.170 --> 00:33:20.605
Will do.

429
00:33:20.630 --> 00:33:23.649
I'll put one ridge on your ass.

430
00:33:23.674 --> 00:33:28.136
Let's roll. That's cool.
Let's get out of here.

431
00:33:29.388 --> 00:33:31.741
Detective. I know I'm new at this...

432
00:33:31.766 --> 00:33:34.869
...but I thought we were supposed
to arrest the bad guys.

433
00:33:34.894 --> 00:33:36.913
Now he owes us one.

434
00:33:36.938 --> 00:33:38.664
So that's how it works.

435
00:33:38.689 --> 00:33:42.835
We let the little fish go. so that
we can catch the big fish later.

436
00:33:42.860 --> 00:33:45.278
I got it. I got it.

437
00:33:47.532 --> 00:33:51.660
You mind if I drive?
I know a shortcut.

438
00:33:54.914 --> 00:33:57.249
You might wanna buckle up.

439
00:34:04.757 --> 00:34:07.652
Are you in a hurry. sir?

440
00:34:07.677 --> 00:34:11.721
Just testing your car.
Balancing out your shit.

441
00:34:13.057 --> 00:34:15.827
When was the last time
you got all up on this thing?

442
00:34:15.852 --> 00:34:19.229
I've never gotten all up
on anything. sir.

443
00:34:19.438 --> 00:34:23.650
Sometimes you gotta feed
some speed to your ride.

444
00:34:25.361 --> 00:34:27.904
Sir! Watch it!

445
00:34:31.200 --> 00:34:34.554
This is the police!
Move your busted-ass vehicle!

446
00:34:34.579 --> 00:34:36.639
Move. move. move. move. move!

447
00:34:36.664 --> 00:34:38.432
This is the LAPD.

448
00:34:38.457 --> 00:34:40.143
We'll pop one in your ass.

449
00:34:40.168 --> 00:34:43.086
We got guns and shit.

450
00:34:43.462 --> 00:34:45.481
I could get used to this!

451
00:34:45.506 --> 00:34:46.524
I like!

452
00:34:46.549 --> 00:34:48.234
I like!

453
00:34:48.259 --> 00:34:50.427
Used to what?

454
00:34:52.346 --> 00:34:56.325
Driving. See. my last partner
did all the driving.

455
00:34:56.350 --> 00:34:59.060
Who was your partner?

456
00:34:59.604 --> 00:35:01.789
I don't wanna talk about it.

457
00:35:01.814 --> 00:35:03.249
Why?

458
00:35:03.274 --> 00:35:08.212
Hey. look. I'm deep. okay? There's
just some places I can't talk about.

459
00:35:08.237 --> 00:35:12.091
We're partners. We gotta communicate.
This thing's like a marriage.

460
00:35:12.116 --> 00:35:14.844
No. this is nothing like a marriage.

461
00:35:14.869 --> 00:35:17.889
What is it like?
- It's more like a one-night stand.

462
00:35:17.914 --> 00:35:21.625
Wham. bam. thank you. officer.

463
00:35:25.254 --> 00:35:27.899
It's like that?
- It's like that.

464
00:35:27.924 --> 00:35:31.611
We're just gonna fight crime
and zip the rest of that shit up.

465
00:35:31.636 --> 00:35:33.279
Are you married?

466
00:35:33.304 --> 00:35:34.947
Girlfriend?
- Not anymore.

467
00:35:34.972 --> 00:35:36.890
What happened?

468
00:35:38.392 --> 00:35:41.186
Work got in the way.

469
00:35:41.270 --> 00:35:43.355
See?

470
00:35:47.527 --> 00:35:50.445
Somebody took out a fire hydrant.

471
00:35:55.993 --> 00:35:59.180
I'll handle this.
- I gotta get back. I got a headache.

472
00:35:59.205 --> 00:36:01.224
We're on duty.

473
00:36:01.249 --> 00:36:05.436
But I need an aspirin.
A big one. like a hockey puck.

474
00:36:05.461 --> 00:36:07.146
Gentlemen. Excuse me.

475
00:36:07.171 --> 00:36:09.732
Could you come here for a second?

476
00:36:09.757 --> 00:36:12.884
Relax. sir.
Just take it easy for a second.

477
00:36:19.684 --> 00:36:22.269
Morning. officer.

478
00:36:24.564 --> 00:36:26.499
Morning. Where's your aspirins?

479
00:36:26.524 --> 00:36:28.751
Back there by the soda machines.

480
00:36:28.776 --> 00:36:30.610
Appreciate it.

481
00:36:40.037 --> 00:36:43.415
I wanna know how the car
hit the fire hydrant.

482
00:36:44.292 --> 00:36:46.435
Open the register!
- Don't shoot!

483
00:36:46.460 --> 00:36:47.770
Come on. man!

484
00:36:47.795 --> 00:36:48.855
Oh. man!

485
00:36:48.880 --> 00:36:51.214
Come on! The safe too!

486
00:36:58.639 --> 00:37:00.473
Come on.

487
00:37:05.688 --> 00:37:09.667
37-King-5.
Shots fired. Request help.

488
00:37:09.692 --> 00:37:13.236
418 West Fifth Street.

489
00:37:19.410 --> 00:37:20.636
Detective Malone!

490
00:37:20.661 --> 00:37:21.971
You okay?

491
00:37:21.996 --> 00:37:23.830
Oh. shit!

492
00:37:25.791 --> 00:37:29.085
Get back! Back! Get back!

493
00:37:32.340 --> 00:37:34.066
Freeze!

494
00:37:34.091 --> 00:37:36.402
Put your hands on the pavement!

495
00:37:36.427 --> 00:37:39.739
Hands on the pavement!
- There is no pavement!

496
00:37:39.764 --> 00:37:41.741
Put them on the Oodles of Noodles.

497
00:37:41.766 --> 00:37:43.951
Put them on the noodles.
- Chicken or beef?

498
00:37:43.976 --> 00:37:45.852
Chicken!

499
00:37:46.479 --> 00:37:47.622
Cool.

500
00:37:47.647 --> 00:37:50.041
Cool is good.

501
00:37:50.066 --> 00:37:51.417
Miles?

502
00:37:51.442 --> 00:37:53.360
Tulley?

503
00:37:57.365 --> 00:37:58.424
What are you doing?

504
00:37:58.449 --> 00:38:00.927
What am I doing?
What are you doing?

505
00:38:00.952 --> 00:38:03.870
I'm freaking working over here.

506
00:38:04.664 --> 00:38:06.349
I'm coming in!

507
00:38:06.374 --> 00:38:08.267
Put the gun down!

508
00:38:08.292 --> 00:38:09.644
Put the gun down!

509
00:38:09.669 --> 00:38:11.395
Detective Malone. talk to me!

510
00:38:11.420 --> 00:38:13.272
Go out the back way!

511
00:38:13.297 --> 00:38:15.358
Go! The back way!

512
00:38:15.383 --> 00:38:17.944
Go out the back way!

513
00:38:17.969 --> 00:38:19.970
Detective. talk to me!

514
00:38:20.847 --> 00:38:23.056
Take 2 steps back!

515
00:38:23.683 --> 00:38:25.767
What the hell? Go!

516
00:38:26.394 --> 00:38:28.311
Hold it!

517
00:38:29.939 --> 00:38:31.982
Hold your fire!

518
00:38:34.360 --> 00:38:36.945
You okay?

519
00:39:00.553 --> 00:39:01.988
Listen. it's a dead end!

520
00:39:02.013 --> 00:39:04.681
No shit!

521
00:39:08.811 --> 00:39:13.356
He's behind those dumpsters.
He's freaking out. He's got a gun.

522
00:39:15.359 --> 00:39:17.319
Back up!

523
00:39:17.612 --> 00:39:22.216
Get SWAT up here! Sharpshooters
can take him off from the roof.

524
00:39:22.241 --> 00:39:24.218
No sharpshooters.

525
00:39:24.243 --> 00:39:26.119
Why the hell not?

526
00:39:27.038 --> 00:39:28.848
What are you doing here. man?

527
00:39:28.873 --> 00:39:31.309
Who's he talking to?
- I don't know.

528
00:39:31.334 --> 00:39:34.729
He high. man. He's hallucinating.
Smoking that shit!

529
00:39:34.754 --> 00:39:37.148
He's high.

530
00:39:37.173 --> 00:39:39.883
Put down the gun and come out!

531
00:39:41.928 --> 00:39:44.280
Hold this. Hold on. I'm going in.

532
00:39:44.305 --> 00:39:45.907
What are you doing?

533
00:39:45.932 --> 00:39:48.308
What are you. crazy?

534
00:39:49.769 --> 00:39:51.913
Miles. what are you doing here?

535
00:39:51.938 --> 00:39:55.082
I just wanna talk to you
before somebody gets hurt!

536
00:39:55.107 --> 00:39:57.043
Please put down the gun!

537
00:39:57.068 --> 00:39:58.920
Son. come on.
- Shut up!

538
00:39:58.945 --> 00:40:00.379
It hurts my heart...

539
00:40:00.404 --> 00:40:03.299
...to see a kid that has
so much potential.

540
00:40:03.324 --> 00:40:06.451
You're smarter than that.
- I'm coming out!

541
00:40:06.494 --> 00:40:10.473
Listen. All right. now. goddamn it!
What are you doing?

542
00:40:10.498 --> 00:40:13.810
What are you doing?
You got me out here in this shit.

543
00:40:13.835 --> 00:40:16.145
How many times I told you...

544
00:40:16.170 --> 00:40:21.150
...forget the safe? Go straight for
the cash drawer. Get in and get out.

545
00:40:21.175 --> 00:40:23.778
He's in the way.
Now I can't even get a shot.

546
00:40:23.803 --> 00:40:25.279
I can't either.

547
00:40:25.304 --> 00:40:27.698
Why are you hitting
mom-and-pop stores anyway?

548
00:40:27.723 --> 00:40:29.909
Look. you're a driver. man.

549
00:40:29.934 --> 00:40:34.205
You got skills. You can be out there
on the road. man. doing your shit.

550
00:40:34.230 --> 00:40:39.234
I'm desperate! I need some money!
And why the freak are we whispering?

551
00:40:40.111 --> 00:40:43.530
Back up. nigger! I saw you!

552
00:40:44.532 --> 00:40:47.176
What are they talking about?
- I don't know.

553
00:40:47.201 --> 00:40:51.722
I'm working on something here.
and you're blowing it for me. man!

554
00:40:51.747 --> 00:40:53.891
I'm sorry. man. I'm messing up.

555
00:40:53.916 --> 00:40:56.185
I'm messing up.
- It's all right.

556
00:40:56.210 --> 00:40:58.437
Look. I'm not mad at you.

557
00:40:58.462 --> 00:41:03.466
But you're gonna have to give me
the gun and let me arrest you.

558
00:41:03.843 --> 00:41:09.806
Come on. man. Listen. I'll give you
10 grand. You know I'm good for it.

559
00:41:10.308 --> 00:41:11.951
I'm thinking like 50. man.

560
00:41:11.976 --> 00:41:15.663
Tulley. 50?
That's pushing it. man! Damn!

561
00:41:15.688 --> 00:41:19.792
Twenty. and you'll spend one night
in jail. That's the best I can do.

562
00:41:19.817 --> 00:41:22.777
That's it. Best I can do.

563
00:41:23.237 --> 00:41:25.965
All right. fine.
But I'm keeping my gun.

564
00:41:25.990 --> 00:41:30.261
You cannot let me arrest you
and keep the gun. man! Come on!

565
00:41:30.286 --> 00:41:33.055
Damn. I just got this. man.
This is hard to find.

566
00:41:33.080 --> 00:41:37.226
But you're gonna have to give up
the gun. Now. what you wanna do?

567
00:41:37.251 --> 00:41:42.839
You wanna give up the gun or you want
them to put about 7 bullets in your ass?

568
00:41:44.175 --> 00:41:46.801
Okay. now give me that gun!

569
00:41:48.137 --> 00:41:50.531
Don't just hand it to me!

570
00:41:50.556 --> 00:41:54.559
I gotta take it from you.
They're watching.

571
00:41:56.145 --> 00:41:58.498
This is gonna hurt a little.

572
00:41:58.523 --> 00:42:00.607
This is gonna hurt.

573
00:42:03.361 --> 00:42:04.712
Jesus!

574
00:42:04.737 --> 00:42:07.173
That's incredible!

575
00:42:07.198 --> 00:42:10.218
And remember:
You don't know me anymore.

576
00:42:10.243 --> 00:42:11.886
I sure don't.

577
00:42:11.911 --> 00:42:13.888
You didn't used to be so violent.

578
00:42:13.913 --> 00:42:16.140
So he's like.
"Carlson. take my jacket."

579
00:42:16.165 --> 00:42:19.685
He's like. "I got to do this."
We're like. "What are you doing?"

580
00:42:19.710 --> 00:42:23.272
He just goes right down the alley.
right up to the guy.

581
00:42:23.297 --> 00:42:26.067
Next thing you know.
he's taking the guy's gun.

582
00:42:26.092 --> 00:42:29.362
Dropped the guy with a punch.
Just leveled him.

583
00:42:29.387 --> 00:42:32.907
I mean. blink and
you would've missed it.

584
00:42:32.932 --> 00:42:34.742
Malone. in my office!

585
00:42:34.767 --> 00:42:37.227
Now!

586
00:42:40.356 --> 00:42:42.566
Not you. Carlson.

587
00:42:46.612 --> 00:42:49.048
I've been looking through your record.

588
00:42:49.073 --> 00:42:51.425
How come I never heard of you?

589
00:42:51.450 --> 00:42:54.011
I was undercover. On the down low.

590
00:42:54.036 --> 00:42:58.456
We need a guy to head Burglary.
Is that the real reason you're here?

591
00:42:58.958 --> 00:42:59.976
Yeah. sure.

592
00:43:00.001 --> 00:43:01.060
It's no secret.

593
00:43:01.085 --> 00:43:06.190
Burglary's been a problem division since
we lost our lead detective last year.

594
00:43:06.215 --> 00:43:09.068
Now. usually we promote
from within the ranks...

595
00:43:09.093 --> 00:43:11.237
...but these guys need someone new.

596
00:43:11.262 --> 00:43:14.556
So if you want the job. you got it.

597
00:43:16.434 --> 00:43:17.785
Excuse me?

598
00:43:17.810 --> 00:43:21.438
You're the new lead detective.
Burglary division.

599
00:43:22.982 --> 00:43:24.941
Me?

600
00:43:26.444 --> 00:43:31.048
Technically. there's a 30-day qualifying
period before I can make it official...

601
00:43:31.073 --> 00:43:35.410
...but with your record I don't think
there'll be any problem.

602
00:43:38.873 --> 00:43:41.708
Well. say something!

603
00:43:43.044 --> 00:43:44.854
Thank you.

604
00:43:44.879 --> 00:43:47.339
Let's party?

605
00:43:49.217 --> 00:43:51.110
What is this? High school?

606
00:43:51.135 --> 00:43:56.532
Listen up. As of now. Detective Malone
is Burglary's new acting lead detective.

607
00:43:56.557 --> 00:43:59.976
Get these processed ASAP.

608
00:44:00.102 --> 00:44:02.562
Thank you.

609
00:44:03.397 --> 00:44:07.543
I got some things I gotta do.
I'll catch up with you later.

610
00:44:07.568 --> 00:44:09.003
I'll take these.

611
00:44:09.028 --> 00:44:11.130
You know what to do with these?
- Sure.

612
00:44:11.155 --> 00:44:13.573
Great. sir. Sorry.

613
00:44:21.833 --> 00:44:24.584
Captain Penelli?
- I'm busy now.

614
00:44:41.227 --> 00:44:44.020
Oh. man!

615
00:45:03.541 --> 00:45:06.126
Shit!

616
00:45:07.295 --> 00:45:09.671
Damn!

617
00:45:20.183 --> 00:45:21.909
What?

618
00:45:21.934 --> 00:45:25.228
How do you want me
to handle the rotation?

619
00:45:25.354 --> 00:45:27.623
I don't understand.
What you mean. "rotation"?

620
00:45:27.648 --> 00:45:30.317
The shifts.

621
00:45:30.443 --> 00:45:34.380
I can't figure out everything
on the first day. all right?

622
00:45:34.405 --> 00:45:37.425
I notice you guys had a leak here.
What's that about?

623
00:45:37.450 --> 00:45:41.203
One of the hot-water pipes burst.
flooded all the vents.

624
00:45:41.412 --> 00:45:44.015
They had to flush out the whole system.

625
00:45:44.040 --> 00:45:46.767
This must be the guy
everybody's talking about.

626
00:45:46.792 --> 00:45:48.895
Captain Penelli. Detective Malone.

627
00:45:48.920 --> 00:45:51.147
Malone. Penelli.

628
00:45:51.172 --> 00:45:56.134
I hear great things.
It's a pleasure to meet you.

629
00:46:01.015 --> 00:46:03.075
Nice to meet you too there. sir!

630
00:46:03.100 --> 00:46:05.519
Very nice to meet you!

631
00:46:06.020 --> 00:46:07.497
Glad to be here.

632
00:46:07.522 --> 00:46:09.940
Gotta go!

633
00:46:12.735 --> 00:46:15.570
He's a strange one.

634
00:46:30.086 --> 00:46:32.879
Place is closed.

635
00:46:32.922 --> 00:46:36.400
I said we're closed.
I should've locked up.

636
00:46:36.425 --> 00:46:38.760
Nice to see you. Lou.

637
00:46:38.970 --> 00:46:40.988
I'm looking for Miles.

638
00:46:41.013 --> 00:46:43.282
Well. I haven't seen him.

639
00:46:43.307 --> 00:46:46.810
I got an important message
from his mother.

640
00:46:47.812 --> 00:46:50.772
Well. I still haven't seen him.

641
00:46:52.525 --> 00:46:54.818
Quiet.

642
00:46:58.865 --> 00:47:01.449
Damn. you're good.

643
00:47:05.788 --> 00:47:08.248
You are good.

644
00:47:50.833 --> 00:47:52.143
Good morning. Listen up.

645
00:47:52.168 --> 00:47:57.214
Word is that Jean LaFleur is bringing
a shipment of heroin through town.

646
00:47:58.549 --> 00:48:00.234
They want him in San Diego.

647
00:48:00.259 --> 00:48:02.570
SDPD's done an excellent job...

648
00:48:02.595 --> 00:48:06.640
...shutting down the harbor
and the airports on him.

649
00:48:13.981 --> 00:48:19.486
Detective Malone just transferred.
He'll head our Burglary division.

650
00:48:19.487 --> 00:48:20.963
Detective...

651
00:48:20.988 --> 00:48:24.157
...tell us a little about your plans.

652
00:48:25.326 --> 00:48:29.079
Well. I plan to fight crime.

653
00:48:33.626 --> 00:48:35.186
You know. shit like that.

654
00:48:35.211 --> 00:48:37.045
Great. then.

655
00:48:37.505 --> 00:48:39.857
Does anybody have any questions
for Malone?

656
00:48:39.882 --> 00:48:41.818
Yeah. I got a question.

657
00:48:41.843 --> 00:48:44.761
What do you think about the P-31?

658
00:48:45.137 --> 00:48:47.722
P-31.

659
00:48:48.850 --> 00:48:49.951
What do you think?

660
00:48:49.976 --> 00:48:52.227
It's a piece of shit.

661
00:48:53.271 --> 00:48:57.375
What I mean is. we've all been having
problems with the P-31. right?

662
00:48:57.400 --> 00:49:02.421
I'm just wondering what the new lead
detective here plans to do about it.

663
00:49:02.446 --> 00:49:06.134
Well. all right.
Well. Diaz. is it? Diaz?

664
00:49:06.159 --> 00:49:09.637
What do you think we should do
about it. Diaz?

665
00:49:09.662 --> 00:49:11.889
I think we should scrap it.

666
00:49:11.914 --> 00:49:16.001
How many people think
we should scrap the P-31?

667
00:49:17.545 --> 00:49:18.896
There it is.

668
00:49:18.921 --> 00:49:21.149
Scrapped. Why?
Because you want it scrapped.

669
00:49:21.174 --> 00:49:25.153
It's out of there. P-31. out of there.
No more. Gone.

670
00:49:25.178 --> 00:49:27.363
You want 31 flavors?

671
00:49:27.388 --> 00:49:30.908
Baskin-Robbins is
where you wanna be. Be cool.

672
00:49:30.933 --> 00:49:33.119
That's my partner.

673
00:49:33.144 --> 00:49:35.020
Detective.

674
00:49:37.231 --> 00:49:39.292
What is it?

675
00:49:39.317 --> 00:49:41.127
I'd like to work with a P-40.

676
00:49:41.152 --> 00:49:43.320
Yeah. the P-40's good.

677
00:49:44.071 --> 00:49:46.615
P-40 it is!

678
00:49:50.203 --> 00:49:52.472
What's he doing?
We just got those things.

679
00:49:52.497 --> 00:49:56.750
He's shaking things up.
Maybe that's exactly what we need.

680
00:50:13.476 --> 00:50:15.578
I'm not a cop.

681
00:50:15.603 --> 00:50:18.331
This Tulley asshole
wants to talk to you.

682
00:50:18.356 --> 00:50:21.107
He's down in Interrogation.

683
00:50:21.901 --> 00:50:24.796
Right away. I'll talk with him.

684
00:50:24.821 --> 00:50:26.756
Interrogation's this way.

685
00:50:26.781 --> 00:50:30.009
Knew that. Is he running his mouth?

686
00:50:30.034 --> 00:50:33.304
Tulley says he has information
about another robbery.

687
00:50:33.329 --> 00:50:37.082
But he'll only talk
to the officer who arrested him.

688
00:50:37.708 --> 00:50:39.977
I'll talk to him. Alone.

689
00:50:40.002 --> 00:50:42.629
We'll be watching.

690
00:50:43.798 --> 00:50:48.260
What's going on? You said
I'd spend one night in jail.

691
00:50:58.271 --> 00:51:01.040
What do you wanna tell me?
What is it?

692
00:51:01.065 --> 00:51:03.334
You said I'd only spend
one night in jail.

693
00:51:03.359 --> 00:51:05.253
It's only been one night.

694
00:51:05.278 --> 00:51:07.463
Well. where's my 50 grand?

695
00:51:07.488 --> 00:51:09.757
I said 20 grand.

696
00:51:09.782 --> 00:51:12.951
Well. maybe it's 50 now! Because...

697
00:51:16.247 --> 00:51:20.059
Detectives. I've been assigned
to Mr. Tulley.

698
00:51:20.084 --> 00:51:22.770
Well. great. That's him.

699
00:51:22.795 --> 00:51:25.940
Oh. my God! What in the world?

700
00:51:25.965 --> 00:51:28.466
Help me!
- What's going on?

701
00:51:28.718 --> 00:51:29.819
Help!

702
00:51:29.844 --> 00:51:32.012
What is this?

703
00:51:34.765 --> 00:51:37.475
Oh. my God!

704
00:51:40.730 --> 00:51:44.500
Take your hands off my client!

705
00:51:44.525 --> 00:51:46.252
It's no use. He ain't talking!

706
00:51:46.277 --> 00:51:49.237
You have your hand over his mouth!

707
00:51:54.202 --> 00:51:58.347
I think we accomplished
enough for one day.

708
00:51:58.372 --> 00:52:01.976
This guy said he has information
on another case.

709
00:52:02.001 --> 00:52:04.562
I wanna know. are you jerking
our chain or not?

710
00:52:04.587 --> 00:52:06.564
I'm not jerking your chain. fella.

711
00:52:06.589 --> 00:52:11.527
This guy Logan owes me
50 thousand dollars.

712
00:52:11.552 --> 00:52:13.696
If I don't get it soon...

713
00:52:13.721 --> 00:52:15.781
...I'm talking!

714
00:52:15.806 --> 00:52:18.826
Who's Logan?
And what do you know about him?

715
00:52:18.851 --> 00:52:22.997
All I can tell you. sir.
is that he's gay. gay. gay!

716
00:52:23.022 --> 00:52:24.791
I've had enough of this!

717
00:52:24.816 --> 00:52:28.878
You certainly have. Come with me.
You'll be hearing from my office!

718
00:52:28.903 --> 00:52:31.923
He made me bite my tongue.
- Come here.

719
00:52:31.948 --> 00:52:33.341
He hit me here.

720
00:52:33.366 --> 00:52:35.676
Next time use a phone book on him.

721
00:52:35.701 --> 00:52:37.595
And they took my shoelace.

722
00:52:37.620 --> 00:52:39.472
Hearing from your office!

723
00:52:39.497 --> 00:52:41.599
Look how she's all over him.

724
00:52:41.624 --> 00:52:45.669
And then he said I was ugly
and I couldn't read good.

725
00:52:49.549 --> 00:52:51.359
Hey. man. What's up?

726
00:52:51.384 --> 00:52:53.611
Some guy's been calling for you.

727
00:52:53.636 --> 00:52:55.947
Who was it?
- Said he's your old partner.

728
00:52:55.972 --> 00:53:00.284
He hopes you found what you're looking for.
Your health benefits expire soon.

729
00:53:00.309 --> 00:53:03.395
Whatever the hell
that's supposed to mean.

730
00:53:06.524 --> 00:53:09.234
Shit!

731
00:53:33.134 --> 00:53:34.968
Bingo!

732
00:53:37.430 --> 00:53:41.349
What is it with you
and the heating ducts. sir?

733
00:53:41.475 --> 00:53:43.536
Cold. You don't feel that?

734
00:53:43.561 --> 00:53:44.787
Very cold.

735
00:53:44.812 --> 00:53:47.415
But I'm busy. What is it you want?

736
00:53:47.440 --> 00:53:50.209
I just tried to pull up your records.

737
00:53:50.234 --> 00:53:52.253
I couldn't find any Malone.

738
00:53:52.278 --> 00:53:55.715
Oh. that's probably because
it was spelled...

739
00:53:55.740 --> 00:53:57.884
When I put the name in the list...

740
00:53:57.909 --> 00:54:00.952
The badge number doesn't exist.

741
00:54:01.871 --> 00:54:03.014
Let me talk to you.

742
00:54:03.039 --> 00:54:07.375
I wanna find out what's going on.
- You're gonna find out.

743
00:54:09.587 --> 00:54:12.005
Now. look.

744
00:54:12.006 --> 00:54:14.192
What I'm about to tell you
is classified.

745
00:54:14.217 --> 00:54:18.362
You tell anyone. I will bust
your ass down to parade detail.

746
00:54:18.387 --> 00:54:20.031
I've been on that detail.

747
00:54:20.056 --> 00:54:24.100
That's permanent horseshit patrol.

748
00:54:26.020 --> 00:54:29.582
This place is a cesspool. But listen.

749
00:54:29.607 --> 00:54:32.025
I'm not from West Covina.

750
00:54:32.026 --> 00:54:33.795
I'm from Internal Affairs.

751
00:54:33.820 --> 00:54:37.030
Oh. man!

752
00:54:40.159 --> 00:54:43.471
All right? This place is a cesspool.

753
00:54:43.496 --> 00:54:46.265
I can't believe I didn't notice!
- It is!

754
00:54:46.290 --> 00:54:48.643
I mean. it doesn't seem like a cesspool.

755
00:54:48.668 --> 00:54:52.104
Believe it. man! There's a lot
of dirty shit going on here!

756
00:54:52.129 --> 00:54:54.148
That's why they sent me here.

757
00:54:54.173 --> 00:54:57.109
I'm the supercop.
They said. "Go. investigate.

758
00:54:57.134 --> 00:54:59.237
Do what you do.
Find another supercop.

759
00:54:59.262 --> 00:55:02.573
Y'all supercop up as a team.
and crack down the shit."

760
00:55:02.598 --> 00:55:04.951
"Crack it down."
That's what I'm here to do.

761
00:55:04.976 --> 00:55:09.437
Are we the only guys that know about it?
We're in the shit now!

762
00:55:13.734 --> 00:55:15.795
You are a good cop. Carlson.

763
00:55:15.820 --> 00:55:18.840
But damn it. man.
you just dug too deep.

764
00:55:18.865 --> 00:55:20.716
What do you want me to do?

765
00:55:20.741 --> 00:55:23.136
Good thing you asked.

766
00:55:23.161 --> 00:55:27.265
Keep your eyes open. Okay?
I need you to be here.

767
00:55:27.290 --> 00:55:29.767
And watch my back. Watch my back.

768
00:55:29.792 --> 00:55:32.937
Got it. sir. I'm out of here.

769
00:55:32.962 --> 00:55:35.463
The other way. Go back.

770
00:55:38.843 --> 00:55:41.052
Shit!

771
00:55:59.614 --> 00:56:01.507
Evidence room.

772
00:56:01.532 --> 00:56:03.533
Shit!

773
00:56:06.120 --> 00:56:09.348
There you are. I just got a call.

774
00:56:09.373 --> 00:56:11.184
413 in progress at the airport.

775
00:56:11.209 --> 00:56:12.602
Go ahead. I'll catch up.

776
00:56:12.627 --> 00:56:16.856
Bullshit! Someone just stole
a museum exhibit from a cargo hold.

777
00:56:16.881 --> 00:56:18.483
That's my problem?

778
00:56:18.508 --> 00:56:20.109
You're lead detective.

779
00:56:20.134 --> 00:56:22.653
Get out there now!

780
00:56:22.678 --> 00:56:27.140
The FBI and Customs Service
is already on the case.

781
00:56:46.285 --> 00:56:48.888
Why are you standing here?
- They won't let me in.

782
00:56:48.913 --> 00:56:50.515
Feds are all over it.

783
00:56:50.540 --> 00:56:53.124
That's bullshit!

784
00:56:53.543 --> 00:56:56.854
These boxes contained
an entire Egyptian temple.

785
00:56:56.879 --> 00:56:59.649
Excuse me. here.
Let me see this. Man!

786
00:56:59.674 --> 00:57:00.983
And who are you?

787
00:57:01.008 --> 00:57:03.820
Malone. LAPD.

788
00:57:03.845 --> 00:57:06.596
Agent Gray. FBI.

789
00:57:06.639 --> 00:57:10.350
We'll let you boys in
after we're done.

790
00:57:12.145 --> 00:57:13.830
Look at all this stuff.

791
00:57:13.855 --> 00:57:18.334
Look. They nearly destroyed all this
stuff and they didn't take none of it.

792
00:57:18.359 --> 00:57:20.670
Look. Officer Malone.

793
00:57:20.695 --> 00:57:22.130
Detective.

794
00:57:22.155 --> 00:57:26.634
You know. you're out of your
jurisdiction and you're over your head.

795
00:57:26.659 --> 00:57:30.096
I'm over my head?
No. I'm over your head...

796
00:57:30.121 --> 00:57:33.039
...because your head's up your ass.

797
00:57:33.916 --> 00:57:38.479
You're interfering with
a federal investigation. officer.

798
00:57:38.504 --> 00:57:41.482
Now. if you and your bunch
wanna feel important...

799
00:57:41.507 --> 00:57:44.610
...you can help secure
the outer perimeter.

800
00:57:44.635 --> 00:57:46.803
Are we clear?

801
00:57:49.098 --> 00:57:51.284
We clear.

802
00:57:51.309 --> 00:57:53.161
And please...

803
00:57:53.186 --> 00:57:57.123
...tell your men not to touch
anything on their way out.

804
00:57:57.148 --> 00:58:00.984
It's like that?
- Yeah. it's like that.

805
00:58:10.161 --> 00:58:12.305
"Head up your ass." That was great.

806
00:58:12.330 --> 00:58:14.849
I couldn't believe you said that.

807
00:58:14.874 --> 00:58:16.976
He called me "officer."

808
00:58:17.001 --> 00:58:22.106
I'm lead detective.
I have 16 citations.

809
00:58:22.131 --> 00:58:23.774
You think that comes easy?

810
00:58:23.799 --> 00:58:26.611
Come on. The guy's nothing
but an FBI asshole.

811
00:58:26.636 --> 00:58:29.822
He thinks we're good for nothing
but sucking down doughnuts.

812
00:58:29.847 --> 00:58:31.991
Let them chase their own
goddamn temple.

813
00:58:32.016 --> 00:58:35.912
They weren't looking for no temple.
They were looking for drugs.

814
00:58:35.937 --> 00:58:37.371
Yes. drugs.

815
00:58:37.396 --> 00:58:39.457
It's the oldest trick in the book.

816
00:58:39.482 --> 00:58:40.750
You smuggle it in...

817
00:58:40.775 --> 00:58:45.338
...boost it before it hits customs.
right? Make it look like a heist.

818
00:58:45.363 --> 00:58:47.465
That's how all the big boys do it.

819
00:58:47.490 --> 00:58:50.843
All they have to do is
look for a truck with a "B" on it.

820
00:58:50.868 --> 00:58:52.345
What do you mean. "B"?

821
00:58:52.370 --> 00:58:54.180
"Bonded."

822
00:58:54.205 --> 00:58:58.643
Bonded trucks can get
into bonded warehouses.

823
00:58:58.668 --> 00:59:00.186
Let me ask you:

824
00:59:00.211 --> 00:59:02.921
How do you know all this stuff?

825
00:59:03.840 --> 00:59:07.610
Did a little work in bonded warehouses.

826
00:59:07.635 --> 00:59:10.279
All right. So what are we waiting for?

827
00:59:10.304 --> 00:59:14.766
Let's do something. all right?
Come on. Call in air support.

828
00:59:15.017 --> 00:59:18.037
Dispatch. this is 37-King-5...

829
00:59:18.062 --> 00:59:22.607
...put me through
to South Bay air support.

830
00:59:27.405 --> 00:59:30.007
<i>10-12. I've got a white panel truck...</i>

831
00:59:30.032 --> 00:59:34.554
<i>...B-961. southbound on Wheeler
near the Manhattan Beach intersection.</i>

832
00:59:34.579 --> 00:59:37.289
Roger. We're close.

833
00:59:40.001 --> 00:59:42.169
Shit!

834
00:59:45.923 --> 00:59:48.192
Now you're in a hurry?

835
00:59:48.217 --> 00:59:53.513
Sometimes you gotta feed a little speed
to your ride. You know what I'm saying?

836
01:00:04.358 --> 01:00:06.485
Here we go.

837
01:00:09.489 --> 01:00:12.157
Check out the driver.

838
01:00:12.283 --> 01:00:15.761
5-feet-6. greasy hair. messy.
very disheveled and...

839
01:00:15.786 --> 01:00:19.539
Are you a hairdresser
or a detective. man?

840
01:00:19.874 --> 01:00:21.642
That's a jailhouse tat.

841
01:00:21.667 --> 01:00:23.686
Driver did a stretch somewhere.

842
01:00:23.711 --> 01:00:25.646
10-12. Requesting backup.

843
01:00:25.671 --> 01:00:28.232
<i>LAPD. this is Agent Gray. FBI.</i>

844
01:00:28.257 --> 01:00:31.777
<i>Stand down. I repeat: Stand down.</i>

845
01:00:31.802 --> 01:00:33.488
This is bullshit!

846
01:00:33.513 --> 01:00:36.991
Screw them. Come on! Let's do it!

847
01:00:37.016 --> 01:00:39.559
Come on. you!

848
01:00:40.478 --> 01:00:41.871
Come on. get the door.

849
01:00:41.896 --> 01:00:43.855
Come on!

850
01:00:44.565 --> 01:00:45.708
Drop your weapons!

851
01:00:45.733 --> 01:00:47.418
Put it down.

852
01:00:47.443 --> 01:00:50.797
All right. don't move! Stand still!

853
01:00:50.822 --> 01:00:52.381
Put it down!

854
01:00:52.406 --> 01:00:55.951
Malone! Take him! He's yours!

855
01:00:56.494 --> 01:00:59.180
Don't you run from me! Don't you run!

856
01:00:59.205 --> 01:01:02.374
Let's see those hands. butterball.

857
01:01:03.543 --> 01:01:04.560
Come here!

858
01:01:04.585 --> 01:01:07.170
You wanna make me run?

859
01:01:11.634 --> 01:01:13.593
Come back here!

860
01:01:32.738 --> 01:01:34.781
Come back here!

861
01:01:37.618 --> 01:01:39.345
Bring your ass here!

862
01:01:39.370 --> 01:01:41.246
Come here!

863
01:01:46.544 --> 01:01:48.396
Come here!

864
01:01:48.421 --> 01:01:51.423
It's okay. Don't worry. I'm a cop.

865
01:01:52.341 --> 01:01:54.551
All right?

866
01:01:54.844 --> 01:01:56.678
Damn!

867
01:02:00.641 --> 01:02:03.077
Don't you know better
than to run from the police?

868
01:02:03.102 --> 01:02:04.120
I do.

869
01:02:04.145 --> 01:02:08.040
You got me tired. I don't like
to get tired. When I get tired...

870
01:02:08.065 --> 01:02:09.917
...I got ass to whoop.

871
01:02:09.942 --> 01:02:13.528
That's what I'm about to do.
Get your ass up!

872
01:02:17.492 --> 01:02:19.010
Bingo.

873
01:02:19.035 --> 01:02:21.661
That's the shit.

874
01:02:25.291 --> 01:02:29.729
We showed them. We showed them. and
that's what I wanted to do. you know?

875
01:02:29.754 --> 01:02:31.772
Put this into evidence.
- Exactly.

876
01:02:31.797 --> 01:02:33.733
Evidence. I'll go up with it.

877
01:02:33.758 --> 01:02:36.152
I want you interrogating
those men right now.

878
01:02:36.177 --> 01:02:38.863
No. See. I need to go up
with this stuff...

879
01:02:38.888 --> 01:02:41.282
...and book it into evidence personally.

880
01:02:41.307 --> 01:02:43.141
Why?

881
01:02:44.060 --> 01:02:47.288
I gotta go through it for clues and shit.

882
01:02:47.313 --> 01:02:50.958
Interrogate the suspects.
Find out where they were going.

883
01:02:50.983 --> 01:02:55.463
Then. when you get them to talk. you can
go through all the evidence you want.

884
01:02:55.488 --> 01:02:58.257
But. sir...

885
01:02:58.282 --> 01:03:03.137
If I get the clue. it'd make
for a better ass-whooping interrogation.

886
01:03:03.162 --> 01:03:06.081
Let's hear it for Detective Malone!

887
01:03:17.552 --> 01:03:20.571
That's it! I want a lawyer.
You cops can't do this.

888
01:03:20.596 --> 01:03:23.181
I got news for you. I ain't a cop.

889
01:03:24.725 --> 01:03:26.369
God. he's good.

890
01:03:26.394 --> 01:03:29.771
I checked.
West Covina never heard of him.

891
01:03:29.772 --> 01:03:32.041
So you know.
- Know what?

892
01:03:32.066 --> 01:03:33.668
He's Internal Affairs.

893
01:03:33.693 --> 01:03:36.003
What are you talking about?
He's not I.A.

894
01:03:36.028 --> 01:03:37.046
He's not?

895
01:03:37.071 --> 01:03:39.322
Hell. no. He's FBI.

896
01:03:39.866 --> 01:03:42.051
But he hates the FBI.

897
01:03:42.076 --> 01:03:45.304
That's to throw you off.
You think this is an accident?

898
01:03:45.329 --> 01:03:49.142
He knew about the heroin from the start.
FBI planted him here.

899
01:03:49.167 --> 01:03:53.104
Thought he'd get first jump on the burglary.
Afraid we'd screw it up.

900
01:03:53.129 --> 01:03:55.839
Pencil-dicks.

901
01:03:58.426 --> 01:04:01.154
You don't get that training
at the academy.

902
01:04:01.179 --> 01:04:03.114
No. that's old school. man.

903
01:04:03.139 --> 01:04:05.891
You're crushing my head!

904
01:04:07.393 --> 01:04:09.412
That's federal government training.

905
01:04:09.437 --> 01:04:13.023
Like Navy SEAL stuff.

906
01:04:14.567 --> 01:04:17.319
Let's go give him a hand.

907
01:04:18.779 --> 01:04:23.033
All right! All right!
I'll talk! Oh. man!

908
01:04:55.858 --> 01:04:57.919
Look at you.

909
01:04:57.944 --> 01:05:02.405
It was all worth it for you. baby.

910
01:05:07.912 --> 01:05:10.288
What are you doing up there?

911
01:05:10.498 --> 01:05:15.478
I'm just so happy that we're keeping
these drugs off the street.

912
01:05:15.503 --> 01:05:18.397
Get over it. They're going
right back out again.

913
01:05:18.422 --> 01:05:19.524
Why?

914
01:05:19.549 --> 01:05:22.944
Because the FBI wants to take it
to their lab right away.

915
01:05:22.969 --> 01:05:25.095
Roll it out.

916
01:05:28.724 --> 01:05:30.034
Malone. come on!

917
01:05:30.059 --> 01:05:32.477
Let's go.

918
01:05:32.979 --> 01:05:35.188
Come on. Malone.

919
01:05:47.410 --> 01:05:49.619
Detective.

920
01:05:49.787 --> 01:05:52.849
That heroin belongs to Jean LaFleur.

921
01:05:52.874 --> 01:05:54.684
We've been after him for 5 years.

922
01:05:54.709 --> 01:05:57.979
He keeps shifting his operations
between the U.S. And Mexico.

923
01:05:58.004 --> 01:06:00.523
We're taking it down to our lab right now.

924
01:06:00.548 --> 01:06:02.275
That's not a good idea.

925
01:06:02.300 --> 01:06:04.217
Why not?

926
01:06:04.844 --> 01:06:06.779
Why don't we just keep it here?

927
01:06:06.804 --> 01:06:11.224
LaFleur doesn't know we have it.
We could use it for bait.

928
01:06:11.601 --> 01:06:13.035
You mean a sting?

929
01:06:13.060 --> 01:06:16.581
Exactly. A sting!

930
01:06:16.606 --> 01:06:20.626
LaFleur expects these drugs
to be in San Diego in 3 hours.

931
01:06:20.651 --> 01:06:24.630
What kind of sting operation can you
get off the ground before then?

932
01:06:24.655 --> 01:06:27.633
The driver told me one of the guys
on the truck was new.

933
01:06:27.658 --> 01:06:29.927
You can replace him with somebody else.

934
01:06:29.952 --> 01:06:34.098
Then catch LaFleur when he goes
to pick up the drugs. Bam! Got him!

935
01:06:34.123 --> 01:06:35.641
Let me get this straight.

936
01:06:35.666 --> 01:06:39.729
You're volunteering to escort
these drugs into the hands...

937
01:06:39.754 --> 01:06:43.065
...of the most dangerous dealer
in the northern hemisphere?

938
01:06:43.090 --> 01:06:44.317
Hell. no!

939
01:06:44.342 --> 01:06:47.010
What do you need to make it work?

940
01:06:47.553 --> 01:06:50.156
Me?
- You're the man for the job!

941
01:06:50.181 --> 01:06:53.242
FBI will have tactical command.
but we'll follow your lead.

942
01:06:53.267 --> 01:06:56.412
It's very brave. Let's go.
There's not much time.

943
01:06:56.437 --> 01:06:58.456
Way to go. Malone. Way to go.

944
01:06:58.481 --> 01:07:03.026
I'm just suggesting some shit.
- We need more men like you!

945
01:07:05.154 --> 01:07:08.382
All right. Hurry up.
Go. Get out of here!

946
01:07:08.407 --> 01:07:10.384
Wait. Hold up. Wait a minute.

947
01:07:10.409 --> 01:07:13.721
You wanted to go.
I'm getting you out of here. Go!

948
01:07:13.746 --> 01:07:16.766
You wouldn't still be here
unless that diamond was here.

949
01:07:16.791 --> 01:07:18.017
I want my cut!

950
01:07:18.042 --> 01:07:21.604
There ain't nothing to cut.
I gotta get the diamond first.

951
01:07:21.629 --> 01:07:23.022
Go get it. I'll wait.

952
01:07:23.047 --> 01:07:26.400
I'm trying to. First. I gotta
run a sting on a drug dealer.

953
01:07:26.425 --> 01:07:27.985
You're a goddamn liar!

954
01:07:28.010 --> 01:07:30.988
Would I make this shit up?
Get out of here!

955
01:07:31.013 --> 01:07:34.325
I'll see you at Lou's tomorrow.
- I wanna talk about this!

956
01:07:34.350 --> 01:07:36.536
I don't know what you're doing...

957
01:07:36.561 --> 01:07:38.246
...but it ain't gonna work!

958
01:07:38.271 --> 01:07:41.106
And let me get my gun back!

959
01:07:46.571 --> 01:07:50.550
Look. Maybe this isn't
a good idea. you know?

960
01:07:50.575 --> 01:07:53.719
This is a great idea. It'll work.
- Brilliant.

961
01:07:53.744 --> 01:07:57.306
LaFleur's looking for this.
- We know what we're doing. detective.

962
01:07:57.331 --> 01:07:59.767
Oh. I'm a detective now.

963
01:07:59.792 --> 01:08:02.169
Give us a level. please.

964
01:08:02.295 --> 01:08:03.938
All right. detective.

965
01:08:03.963 --> 01:08:08.526
The objective is to have these men
see you as if you were one of them:

966
01:08:08.551 --> 01:08:12.488
A member of the criminal underworld.
It's important your speech...

967
01:08:12.513 --> 01:08:17.535
...and your behavior are congruent with
their expectation of a fellow criminal.

968
01:08:17.560 --> 01:08:20.413
I get it. Sort of "walk the walk."

969
01:08:20.438 --> 01:08:21.873
That's right.

970
01:08:21.898 --> 01:08:24.625
You have to look. act...

971
01:08:24.650 --> 01:08:27.128
...and even think like a criminal.

972
01:08:27.153 --> 01:08:29.172
Change your speech patterns too.

973
01:08:29.197 --> 01:08:33.551
Criminals like to use slang terminology
and profanity and so forth...

974
01:08:33.576 --> 01:08:37.138
...especially with regard to police
and authority figures.

975
01:08:37.163 --> 01:08:40.099
You mean like. "Shut the hell up.
you dickless FBI..."

976
01:08:40.124 --> 01:08:42.101
That's right.
- "You stupid ass."

977
01:08:42.126 --> 01:08:43.686
That'll do.
- "You tight..."

978
01:08:43.711 --> 01:08:45.921
Enough!

979
01:08:46.714 --> 01:08:47.982
All right. listen up.

980
01:08:48.007 --> 01:08:49.942
LaFleur's a killer.

981
01:08:49.967 --> 01:08:55.722
If he senses anything amiss. Malone
is gonna be in one hell of a tight spot.

982
01:09:00.102 --> 01:09:03.706
If anything happens to me.
forget everything I ever told you.

983
01:09:03.731 --> 01:09:06.000
You mean about Internal Affairs?

984
01:09:06.025 --> 01:09:08.127
No. Carlson. I mean about everything.

985
01:09:08.152 --> 01:09:10.296
Detective. saddle up.

986
01:09:10.321 --> 01:09:12.906
Good luck.

987
01:09:16.369 --> 01:09:19.430
Carlson. remember. Forget it!

988
01:09:19.455 --> 01:09:21.581
Time to go.

989
01:09:23.167 --> 01:09:24.685
Detective.

990
01:09:24.710 --> 01:09:28.689
If my client gets a scratch
on him while he's in your custody...

991
01:09:28.714 --> 01:09:33.903
...I'll see your badge is revoked
and you're thrown in jail. Okay?

992
01:09:33.928 --> 01:09:36.471
You can't touch me.

993
01:09:38.599 --> 01:09:43.311
He'll be fine. counselor.
Malone. let's get this show on the road.

994
01:09:43.354 --> 01:09:46.022
Drive. Buckle up.

995
01:09:48.067 --> 01:09:49.127
Give me video.

996
01:09:49.152 --> 01:09:50.753
<i>Let's get one thing straight.</i>

997
01:09:50.778 --> 01:09:53.673
This is my side here
and that's your side there.

998
01:09:53.698 --> 01:09:56.592
Stay on your side
and I'm gonna stay on mine.

999
01:09:56.617 --> 01:09:57.760
Gentlemen.

1000
01:09:57.785 --> 01:09:59.512
Keep the chatter to a minimum.

1001
01:09:59.537 --> 01:10:02.932
You don't like the show.
change the channel.

1002
01:10:02.957 --> 01:10:06.126
And keep this channel clear.

1003
01:10:08.880 --> 01:10:11.149
Who is this guy?

1004
01:10:11.174 --> 01:10:13.258
That's Malone.

1005
01:10:13.968 --> 01:10:15.987
I can't drive if you do that.

1006
01:10:16.012 --> 01:10:18.388
Drive!

1007
01:10:37.074 --> 01:10:39.493
We're coming up on our exit.

1008
01:10:40.411 --> 01:10:44.664
All units. this is Gray.
Fall back and keep your distance.

1009
01:10:53.966 --> 01:10:55.610
We're approaching the site.

1010
01:10:55.635 --> 01:10:58.970
LAPD. take the south side.
We'll take the north.

1011
01:11:22.954 --> 01:11:25.723
They're headed into warehouse 3.

1012
01:11:25.748 --> 01:11:26.808
Focus in.

1013
01:11:26.833 --> 01:11:28.667
Closer.

1014
01:11:35.967 --> 01:11:37.026
This is it.

1015
01:11:37.051 --> 01:11:39.278
You sure?
- Yeah. Warehouse 3.

1016
01:11:39.303 --> 01:11:43.783
All right. Benny. sit tight
and keep your mouth shut.

1017
01:11:43.808 --> 01:11:46.017
Thanks for the tip.

1018
01:11:51.649 --> 01:11:53.859
What's Malone doing?

1019
01:12:00.658 --> 01:12:02.760
<i>They're coming in behind you.</i>

1020
01:12:02.785 --> 01:12:05.704
